			//- section
				h4 
				aside.notes.
					This happened already with advertising, where two similar adverts are tested with the public and the most effective advert (the one that converts into more sales) is favoured over the weaker one. 

					Thanks to the internet, this can happen millions of times per second, with thousands of AB tests running in sequence, giving a real-time understanding of how an advert is performing.

					Many public digital ad campaigns have cameras that track user behaviours : how long people are staying to read it, their age, gender. It is not unreasonable to expect that an agent-created advert could instantly deliver the perfect advert directly to the person consuming it.

					As robots care not for your carefully crafted banner adverts, new industries will be created that advertise directly to the robots.

			section 
				h4: mark Memory
				h4 Context
				aside.notes 
					p The average human can only remember 7 pieces of information at any one time. Trying to remember an extra piece will make you forget one of the original ones! 
					
					p Large language models alone lack the ability to experiment or to learn from their experiences, meaning they lack the ability to form insight. 

			section 
				video( data-autoplay, muted, src="/static/talk/bbc-micro-edit.mp4").full-size.wallpaper.monochromatic 
				aside.notes 
					p Computers have the same forgetfullness problem, they can't remember everything, and define what they can remember as their "context window", as the term memory was already being used for something else.

					p This is the reason for their lack of continuity and awareness.

					p People use these tools with high confidence in their abilities usually to ask questions on topics they are unsure about.
			
					p Instead of filling up the model's memory with memes, imagine their potential if they became experts in one field. 
					
					p A medical domain expert trained by reading medical books, scientific papers, clinical journals, datasets and reports?

					p After all, Nobody wants a sassy doctor.

					p For domain-specific knowledge, the currently recommended way of teaching a robot is by creating a human-authored guidebook with all the trappings discovered through years of personal experience.
	
