				aside.notes
					p Biases are inherent in all data sets.

					p Frank Rosenblatt invented the single-layer neural network, the Perceptron, in 1957, which gave text weight by attributing bias, giving computers better comprehension (understanding) skills.

					p The more data you have, the less control there can be of the process and output.

					p Good data is data that has been designed for the purpose of communication. 

					p Fact-rich, educational, and easily summarised.

