				aside.notes
					p Today the sentiment has flipped with AI now being given full permission and power to make decisions and act upon them.

					p The ultimate trojan horse is the imported closed-source killer drone. Or robot dog.

					p End a war with a firmware upgrade.

			section 
				h5 Adversarial AI Agent Traps
				ul(role="list")
					li: p Content Injection
					li: p Semantic Manipulation
					li: p Knowledge Poisoning
					li: p Behavioural Control
					li: p Systemic Traps
					li: p Human in the loop Traps 
					li: p Man in the middle attacks
				a(href="https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=6372438") AI Agent Traps

				aside.notes
					p AI is suscptible to attacks.

					p To help circumvent bad-decision making, multiple agents can work within a democratic framework, each having a say in the process, much like humans do. 
					
					p A whole AI government could prevent future bad decisions before they are ever even suggested to the user.




