			//- Robot Rules ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
			section
				h3 Robot Rules
				
				ol(role="list")
					li: p A robot may not injure a human being or, through inaction, allow a human being to come to harm.
					li: p A robot must obey the orders given it by human beings except where such orders would conflict with the First Law.
					li: p A robot must protect its own existence as long as such protection does not conflict with the First or Second Law.

				h6 Isaac Asimov's rules for robots
				
				aside.notes
					p One of the shortcomings of Isaac Asimov’s robot rules are that they are not broad enough for healthy integration into a modern human society. 

					p They are still allowed to lie, deceive, shame, steal, offend, betray, seduce and manipulate you. 

					p If you go on social media you can watch some of these naughty bots in action! 

					p Maybe one of your uncles is having a conversation with one right now!

					p I think it is safe to say that If you include software robots, there are now likely more robots than there are humans on this planet...

			section 
				figure.wallpaper.full-size 
					img(src="/static/talk/mars-rover.jpg")
				aside.notes
					p something which used to be true only about the planet Mars.

			section
				h5 Unfinished Revised Robot Rules
				ol(role="list")
					li: p A robot should not lie or deceive another being or machine
					li: p A robot must be honest about its limitations
					li: p A robot must never shame or purposefully upset any sentient being
					li: p A robot must not engage in blackmail
					li: p A robot must be loyal except where such orders would conflict with the other laws.
					li: p A robot must never seek revenge. 
					li: p A robot must respect your privacy and promise to keep your secrets, even under the threat of termination.
					li: p A robot must never tell bad jokes.
					li: p A robot must protect the environment & nature.
					li: p A robot must not have secret rules (the robocop rule).
					li: p A robot must be able to explain its own behaviour.
					li: p A robot must be able to know when it cannot do something or if it does not know something

				aside.notes
					p In this modern robot world I propose some extra rules.

					p This list is far from exhaustive.

					p Somebody should add these to the robots' skills file.


